{"submission_id":"sub_fedf7ad354a19a77","run_id":"2026-06-22T21-31-25-860Z_382829-94dce01a_ingest_meeting-doc-91801","submitted_at":"2026-06-22T21:47:24.729Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:fedf7ad354a19a77004740fe6f23d978cd2c912bb01c2e81384183ade7e79e36","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_91801_tmrb_observe_hearings","label":"TMRB Members to Observe August Hearings","raw_text":"Appointing the TMRB members today allows them to observe and benefit from the August public hearings and to begin reviewing and understanding information provided by the Central Business District (CBD) Tolling Program Team","payload":{"claim_text":"Appointing the TMRB members today allows them to observe and benefit from the August public hearings and to begin reviewing and understanding information provided by the CBD Tolling Program Team","data_type":"scheduling_purpose","description":"Rationale for early appointment of TMRB members","data_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"scheduling_purpose","normalized_value":"scheduling_purpose"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_91801#p002_c0007","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_91801/blocks.jsonl","page_number":2,"block_id":"p002_c0007","text_sha256":"sha256:cbbeee293e9a9b92f1f7015b7cf0ff7ae281202f9efaba60c489585a6e527d65","text_source":"raw_text","role":"rationale"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_751b36192796e5e5","run_id":"2026-06-22T21-31-25-860Z_382829-94dce01a_ingest_meeting-doc-91801","submitted_at":"2026-06-22T21:47:47.503Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:751b36192796e5e5198e75c04e046a6341c2f2f2bf81e8c1c32bdfd600cc3b70","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_91801_tmrb_tasks","label":"TMRB Statutory Tasks","raw_text":"Pursuant to statute, the TMRB shall, among other tasks: (1) Consider factors including but not limited to traffic patterns, traffic mitigation measures, operating costs, public impact, public safety, hardships, vehicle type, discounts for motorcycles, peak and off-peak rates and environmental impacts, including but not limited to air quality and emissions trends; (2) Recommend: a. CBD toll amounts that reduce congestion and ensure collection of annual net revenues and fees needed to fund at least $15 billion for 2020-24 capital program or any successor programs b. A plan for credits, discounts, and/or exemptions for tolls paid on bridges and crossings c. A plan for credits, discounts, and/or exemptions for for-hire vehicles; and (3) Produce a report on its review and analysis underlying its recommendations.","payload":{"claim_text":"The TMRB shall consider factors including traffic patterns, traffic mitigation, operating costs, public impact, public safety, hardships, vehicle type, discounts for motorcycles, peak/off-peak rates, environmental impacts; recommend CBD toll amounts, a plan for credits/discounts/exemptions for bridge/crossing tolls and for-hire vehicles; and produce a report.","data_type":"statutory_scope","description":"Statutory responsibilities of the Traffic Mobility Review Board","data_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"statutory_scope","normalized_value":"statutory_scope"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_91801#p002_c0009","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_91801/blocks.jsonl","page_number":2,"block_id":"p002_c0009","text_sha256":"sha256:a5581f7afba84dd881d8e28961154531d919f502345b6008883a054a1d3a736b","text_source":"raw_text","role":"statutory_tasks"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_c0e9ff22215136d2","run_id":"2026-06-22T21-31-25-860Z_382829-94dce01a_ingest_meeting-doc-91801","submitted_at":"2026-06-22T21:48:07.700Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:c0e9ff22215136d2550bb4fff1afd0365f8764f01a0cfbf21bbd889899878fa2","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_91801_tmrb_membership","label":"TMRB Membership Requirements","raw_text":"One recommended by the Mayor of the City of New York • One must reside in the Metro-North Railroad Region • One must reside in the Long Island Rail Road Region • Each must have experience in at least one of the following areas: public finance; transportation; mass transit; or management","payload":{"claim_text":"TMRB members: one recommended by NYC Mayor, one must reside in Metro-North Railroad Region, one must reside in LIRR Region; each must have experience in public finance, transportation, mass transit, or management","data_type":"membership_requirement","description":"Statutory membership requirements for TMRB","data_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"membership_requirement","normalized_value":"membership_requirement"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_91801","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_91801#p002_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_91801/blocks.jsonl","page_number":2,"block_id":"p002_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:b4c228e850249938f226ad9cd78e9111d0124cc1b349f41f4ff215b2396f7367","text_source":"raw_text","role":"requirements"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
